Part E: Multi-Step Word Problems

Show all work and label your answer.

A store sold 4,298 pencils on Monday and 3,756 on Tuesday. How many pencils were sold in total?

A baker made 9,450 cookies and packed them into boxes of 15. How many boxes did she fill?

A family drove 2,864 miles on a road trip. They drove 965 miles the first day and 728 miles the second. How many miles were left to drive?

A classroom has 28 students. Each student brings 4 cans for a food drive. How many cans are collected?